flavorText: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it's not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer's orders with complete nonchalance.
If interrupted while miming, it will slap around the enemy with its broad hands.
This pitiless Pokémon commands a group of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.
Normally, it has 80 poisonous tentacles. The longer one has been alive, the fewer tentacles it will have.
When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.
Long considered a mythical Pokémon until recently, when a small colony was found living underwater.
It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.
Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.
If it digs at an incredible pace, it may snap off its spike and claws. They grow back in a day.
Its legs are short, but its hooves are wide and flat, allowing it to easily walk over snow.
Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.
It blocks opponents' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.
It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.
It cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.
When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.
A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokémon are always after it, but it's not intelligent enough to care.
Poochyena's nose can identify any scent. It's very useful for reconnaissance.
Digs large sinkholes in the ground and tries to trap its enemies in them.
The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.
Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.
The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.
It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.
It can live in or out of water. When out of water, it constantly sweats to keep its body slimy.
Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.
It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.
When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue, then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.
This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.
There's a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.
When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
Even fast-swimming fish Pokémon can be disabled by Golduck. It brings them to a standstill and seizes them.
This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600º F.
It floats using its well-developed floatation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.
The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.
The latest research has determined that there are over 20 possible arrangements of the patterns on its stomach.
It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.
Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.
After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns.
It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
Sneaks up silently on its prey and attacks it from behind, sometimes killing it with one bite.
If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.
It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
It lures prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.
This legendary Pokémon is said to freeze the water in the air during winter, causing snow.
It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.
The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.
It's protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokémon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn't care.
When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.
It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.
Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It's a highly favored tropical snack.
A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.
It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.
The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membranes and released while it is gliding.

Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 F.

At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.
Its body is light, and its legs are incredibly powerful. It can clear Ayers Rock in one leap.
A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.
It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.
Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather's body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.
It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.
Although it naturally prefers colder locales, Delibird in Alola seem able to withstand the heat to a certain extent.
Very protective of its sprawling territory, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.
A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.
Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.
It uses its scaly, rugged body to seal the entrance of its nest and protect its young from predators.
Although its legs are short, its rugged hooves prevent it from slipping, even on icy ground.
It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

This legendary Pokémon is said to be present wherever there is a lightning storm.
